      <item>
        <title>D3 Mapping</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href=&quot;http://d3js.org/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;D3&lt;/a&gt; JavaScript library is an awesome tool to create responsive and interative visualizations. In order to sharpen my own D3 skills and to practice incorporating Makefiles into my workflow, I decided to visualize the &lt;a href=&quot;http://factfinder.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?pid=ACS_13_5YR_B19313&amp;prodType=table&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;aggregate income of the counties&lt;/a&gt; in the US using a &lt;a href=&quot;http://indiemapper.com/app/learnmore.php?l=proportional_symbols&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;graduated symbol map&lt;/a&gt; (bubble map). Mouse over the bubbles for more information about each bubble.&lt;/p&gt;

