      <item>
        <title>Recommendation Systems</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;The accurate item and music recommendations of &lt;a href=&quot;http://amazon.com&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Amazon.com&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://pandora.com&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Pandora.com&lt;/a&gt; respectively, have always astounded me. Each system is unique -- tailored and optimized with different considerations in mind. In order to understand how these &lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Recommender_system&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;recommendation systems&lt;/a&gt; work, I decided build my own.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using the dataset provided by the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.yelp.com/dataset_challenge/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Yelp Dataset Challenge&lt;/a&gt;, I built a basic Recommendation System using &lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Collaborative_filtering&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;collaborative filtering&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This recommendation system is an ongoing project that will push me to dive deeper and build more sophisticated recommenders while sharpening my &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.python.org/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;python&lt;/a&gt; skills.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please feel free to take a look at the recommendation system I have built so far here: &lt;a href=&quot;http://nbviewer.ipython.org/gist/henryachen/9d61ad38e10c4e43f1fb&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Recommendation System&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
